cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC

This paper deals with the task of quantifying perceived face similarity between a pair of faces, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset and network architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of dealing with subjective opinions, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
